Put the daal in a heavy-based saucepan, pour in 750ml/1pt 7fl oz water and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat then simmer for about one hour, or until the lentils are really soft.Heat the oil in a large pan.  Add the mustard seeds, turmeric, cumin, asafoetida or fennel seeds, ginger, chillies and curry leaves and fry for 2-3 minutes.when the daal is cooked add to the pan and stir in the spinach and spring onions.Heat for a further two minutes, season, then serve.